                                 <locus from="22r" to="25v"/> IV(4/fols. 22r-25v)</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is worn. Some folios are damaged by water
                           (esp. fols. 2, 3, 4, 5).
 The Ms. has been resewn. Empty holes are
                           visible in the centrefold of quire II (s. <locus from="9v" to="10r">9v-10r</locus>).</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="11">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>112</height>
                              <width>108</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">13</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">15</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">25</dim>
                              <dim type="right">15</dim>
                              <dim type="left">10</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">13</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data for <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, but the proportions
                              throughout the Ms. are irregular.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling">Data for <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, but the number
                              greatly varies throughout the Ms.</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern: 1A-1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are visible.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> In some folios, the script does not follow the ruling
                              lines (esp. <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 2v, 3r, 4r, 23r).</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular. The handwriting is characterized by
                           angular, broad letters'
                           shapes.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red.</seg> The scribe was possibly <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12060AsfaKrestos">ʾA[ṣ]fa Krǝstos</persName> who is
                        mentioned on <locus target="#25vb">25vb</locus> in the colophon of the work.
                        The angular hand is similar in style to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11077Zadengel">Zadǝngǝl</persName> of 
                        <ref type="mss" target="ESmr040">MR-040</ref>.<date>19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; incipit; name of the scribe;
                           directives to the ministers and their abbreviations; titles of the books
                           to be read; ʾǝgale, qǝbāʾ; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     
                  </handDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
